# EXAMPLE.md — How to Add Sections to This App

This file shows concrete, copy-paste examples for extending the app with new sections and state.

---

## Example 1: Minimal Static Section

The simplest possible section — no props, no state, just content.

**`src/components/sections/HelloSection.tsx`**
```tsx
export default function HelloSection() {
  return (
    <section className="section-card hello-section">
      <h3>Hello World</h3>
      <p>This is a new section.</p>
    </section>
  );
}
```

**Register it in `src/App.tsx`** — add the import at the top with the other section imports:
```tsx
import HelloSection from './components/sections/HelloSection';
```

Then add it into the render tree. Find the `tab-content--showcase-flow` div and add your wrapper:
```tsx
<div className="tab-content tab-content--showcase-flow">
  {/* Add your section here, before or after existing ones */}
  <div className="showcase-flow-item showcase-flow-item--hello">
    <HelloSection />
  </div>

  <div className="showcase-flow-item showcase-flow-item--hero">
    <HeroSection ... />
  </div>
  {/* ... rest of sections */}
</div>
```

**Add styles in `src/global.css`:**
```css
.hello-section {
  padding: 2rem;
}

.hello-section h3 {
  color: #fcd312; /* WC3 gold */
  font-family: 'Friz Quadrata', serif;
  margin-bottom: 1rem;
}
```

